Bring a #large pot{} of @salt{} water to a boil. Wash and dry produce.

Halve, peel, and thinly slice @shallot{1%unit}. Remove and discard any large
stems from half the @kale{4%oz} leaves; thinly slice leaves. Peel and mince or
grate @garlic{1%clove}.

Heat a large drizzle of @olive oil{} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add
shallot and cook until slightly softened, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Add kale and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring, until tender,
~{5-7%minutes}. > TIP: If needed, add a splash of water to help soften kale.

Stir in garlic and another drizzle of olive oil. Cook until fragrant,
~{30%seconds} more.

Turn off heat. Remove from pan; set aside.

Once water is boiling, gently add @mushroom ravioli{9%oz} to #pot{}, then reduce
heat to low. Cook, stirring occasionally, until tender and floating to the top,
~{3-4%minutes}. Reserve ½ cup pasta cooking water, then drain.

While ravioli cook, melt @butter{2%tbsp} in pan used for kale over medium heat.

> 4 TBSP butter for 4 servings.

Once butter has melted, add @walnuts{1/2%oz}. Cook, stirring, until walnuts
smell toasty and butter is foamy and flecked with amber brown bits,
~{2-3%minutes}.

Add @bacon{4%oz} to pan and cook until crispy, ~{5-7%minutes}.

Add kale mixture to pan with walnuts.

Stir in @veggie stock concentrate{1%unit}, @crème fraîche{2%tbsp}, and
¼ cup reserved pasta cooking water.

> ⅓ cup pasta cooking water for 4 servings.

Bring to a simmer, then stir in ravioli. Cook, stirring, until ravioli are
thoroughly coated in sauce, ~{1-2%minutes}. (Add more pasta cooking water a
splash at a time if needed.) Season with salt and pepper. Turn off heat.

Divide pasta between bowls. Sprinkle with @Parmesan cheese{3%tbsp} and serve.

> Pork is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.